http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Regulations-on-rail-traffic-on-January-27/article14017139.ece

In connection with the ongoing track-doubling work on Vaikom Road and girder change on the Mullampilavilthodu Bridge near Mavelikara, there will be rail traffic regulation on January 27The following trains have been cancelled. Train 56387 Kayamkulam passenger leaving Ernakulam at 11.30 a.m. and its return trip (56388) leaving Kayamkulam at 5 p.m. and 66300 Ernakulam MEMU leaving Kollam Junction at 7.40 a.m. and its return trip (66301) from Ernakulam at 2.40 p.m.The following trains have been diverted: 16382 Kanyakumari-Mumbai CST Express and 16649 Mangaluru-Nagercoil Parasuram Express will be diverted via Alappuzha with stoppages at Ernakulam Junction, Cherthala, Alappuzha, Ambalappuzha, and Haripad. Train 17230 Hyderabad-Thiruvananthapuram Sabari Express will be detained at Piravam Road for 2 hours. Train 12625 Thiruvananthapuram-New Delhi Kerala Express will be detained for 75 minutes between Thiruvananthapuram and Kayamkulam. Train 22113 Lokmanyatilak–Kochuveli Biweekly Express will be detained at Piravom Road for 35 minutes.Special stopsIn connection with the festival at St. Mary’s Forane Church at Ettumanur, the following trains are provided with special stoppage at Ettumanur on January 24 and 25. The departure time at Ettumanur for these trains are given in brackets.Train 16303 Ernakulam-Thiruvananthapuram Vanchinad Express (5.53 a.m.), 16304 Thiruvananthapuram-Ernakulam Vanchinad Express (9 p.m.), 16630 Mangaluru-Thiruvananthapuram Malabar Express (4.21 a.m.), and 16348, Mangaluru-Thiruvananthapuram Express (12.31 midnight).